  "text": "In terms of the filtering of irrelevant information, the pattern found in this study was Alone,Neutral,Incongruent, which is consistent with previous studies [CITATION_1] . The explanation that has been provided for this is that as the distracting set gets more challenging, there is an increased demand on filtering [CITATION_2] . This study shows that anodal and cathodal tDCS both modulate cognitive and motor tasks. They had a consistent effect on results independent of the site of stimulation (anodal improved and cathodal decreased task performance), suggesting that the cortical stimulation is modulating this highly engaged network involved in set shifting.",
